The paper discusses a computer program for generating Earth Observation Level 2 products from multispectral images, which involves image processing, machine learning, and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions a decision tree and a quantitative measure of categorical variable pair association, which are related to machine learning and data analysis, respectively. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with color naming and land cover classification, which are related to natural language processing and information retrieval, respectively. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories.
